<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xml:id="tbxLoader" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>tbxLoader</refname>
        <refpurpose>return a toolbox loader path for top-level loading</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
p = tbxLoader(name)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>Returns the path of the toolbox <literal>loader.sce</literal>. Typing <literal>exec(tbxLoader(&quot;cgal&quot;))</literal> at the prompt loads the toolbox at base scope, making its macros available immediately in the current session.</para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
exec(tbxLoader("cgal"));
]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
